Crown of Thorns chords used, standard tuning

Intro / Verses 1, 2, 3 / Choruses 1, 2
     Asus4   A   Gsus4   G     G5
e|-----X-----X-----X-----X-----X-----|
B|-----5-----5-----3-----3-----3-----|
G|-----7-----6-----5-----4-----0-----|
D|-----7-----7-----5-----5-----0-----|
A|-----X-----X-----X-----X-----5-----|
E|-----5-----5-----3-----3-----3-----|
(NB: the main verse and chorus progressions are basically Hendrix-esque power chords, 
use your thumb on the bass E string and to mute the A string.  Many interpretations 
don’t include the bass notes, but I think it makes the song sound fuller especially if you’re solo,
short a guitar or playing on acoustic.  G5 can also be played 3X503X, but I think the version above
is better differentiated from the G.  I often let the e and A string ring in the A chords and the
e string ring in the G chords for fullness.  There are many good tab versions of the usual three 
string version of the verse/chorus part of the song, this is how I play it.)

