(NB: the first two notes of the last lick, the A pentatonic scale on the E string, might 
actually be just a palm muted 5-7 on the A string, but I think this sounds closer – also,
the first and final harmonic note can also be played on fret 12 on the B string or fret 4 on the G string 
or any other variant of B – it is just feedback but tonally a B note – harmonic was the closest I could find.)

